Title: 256LOL - An x86 Assembler in 256 LOC
Description: For the first “real” post in this blog, we’ll build an x86 assembler in less than 256 lines of C code.  Obviously, it won’t implement every x86 instruction, but it will implement a surprisingly useful subset: data movement, control flow, integer arithmetic, bitwise operations, and function calls.  We won’t be able to run the generated machine code yet (that’s coming in a later blog post), but we’ll be in a good position to do so.
